    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Axes or chisels from the Middle Bronze Age, successors to the flanged axe. They consist of two parts, the blade with sharp cutting edge and the handle, set in a split handle, separated by a transverse rib to keep the handle from splitting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
